<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ELFT&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><span class="doxyHighlight">std::vector&lt;typename ELFT::Rel&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/elffile/#af6fe298454e5320427d65c40da7981aa"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/elffile/#af6fe298454e5320427d65c40da7981aa">ELFFile&lt;ELFT&gt;::decode&#95;relrs</a>(Elf&#95;Relr&#95;Range <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/elffile/#abfc0395a4aa4e229de6ff4f2c8c8f63c">relrs</a>)</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This function decodes the contents of an SHT&#95;RELR packed relocation</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// section.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Proposal for adding SHT&#95;RELR sections to generic-abi is here:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/generic-abi/bX460iggiKg</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#aa438ee4f7cc143674ffb81a41c01fcb2"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The encoded sequence of Elf64&#95;Relr entries in a SHT&#95;RELR section looks</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// like &#91; AAAAAAAA BBBBBBB1 BBBBBBB1 ... AAAAAAAA BBBBBB1 ... &#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#abf0867b6082e1e0408b1b5d8301f27e2"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// i.e. start with an address, followed by any number of bitmaps. The address</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// entry encodes 1 relocation. The subsequent bitmap entries encode up to 63</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// relocations each, at subsequent offsets following the last address entry.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The bitmap entries must have 1 in the least significant bit. The assumption</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// here is that an address cannot have 1 in lsb. Odd addresses are not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// supported.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Excluding the least significant bit in the bitmap, each non-zero bit in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the bitmap represents a relocation to be applied to a corresponding machine</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// word that follows the base address word. The second least significant bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// represents the machine word immediately following the initial address, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// each bit that follows represents the next word, in linear order. As such,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a single bitmap can encode up to 31 relocations in a 32-bit object, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 63 relocations in a 64-bit object.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This encoding has a couple of interesting properties:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 Looking at any entry, it is clear whether it&#39;s an address or a bitmap:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    even means address, odd means bitmap.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 Just a simple list of addresses is a valid encoding.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#af6fe298454e5320427d65c40da7981aa"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="367"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Elf&#95;Rel Rel;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="368" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#aa1027abe2321f5eee653435e5305ddab"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Rel.r&#95;info = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00369" /><CodeLine lineNumber="369"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Rel.setType(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/elffile/#a504594efdb5d22d6233ba933e550bc2a">getRelativeRelocationType</a>(), </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="370" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#a85a04b6f06b8f42bce6a666eee85d745"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::vector&lt;Elf&#95;Rel&gt; Relocs;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="372"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Word type: uint32&#95;t for Elf32, and uint64&#95;t for Elf64.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="373" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/objcopy/elf/elffile/#a0752ad646759ea4a034a218da571ab8b"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">using </span><span class="doxyHighlight">Addr = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ELFT::uint;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="374"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00375" /><CodeLine lineNumber="375"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Addr <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sampleprof/#a702f69807459cc25db5754a5f179d3fcaf6fbeb8fa9f451468611536b00878d41">Base</a> = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00376" /><CodeLine lineNumber="376"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Elf&#95;Relr R : <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/elffile/#abfc0395a4aa4e229de6ff4f2c8c8f63c">relrs</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00377" /><CodeLine lineNumber="377"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ELFT::uint Entry = R;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00378" /><CodeLine lineNumber="378"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ((Entry &amp; 1) == 0) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00379" /><CodeLine lineNumber="379"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Even entry: encodes the offset for next relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00380" /><CodeLine lineNumber="380"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Rel.r&#95;offset = Entry;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Relocs.push&#95;back(Rel);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Set base offset for subsequent bitmap entries.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sampleprof/#a702f69807459cc25db5754a5f179d3fcaf6fbeb8fa9f451468611536b00878d41">Base</a> = Entry + </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(Addr);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Odd entry: encodes bitmap for relocations starting at base.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Addr <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a05f5b9a11bdcc5feba62899f95dcf878a3134224cba2545bc57954d3b072aebb4">Offset</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sampleprof/#a702f69807459cc25db5754a5f179d3fcaf6fbeb8fa9f451468611536b00878d41">Base</a>; (Entry &gt;&gt;= 1) != 0; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a05f5b9a11bdcc5feba62899f95dcf878a3134224cba2545bc57954d3b072aebb4">Offset</a> += </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(Addr))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ((Entry &amp; 1) != 0) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><span class="doxyHighlight">          Rel.r&#95;offset = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a05f5b9a11bdcc5feba62899f95dcf878a3134224cba2545bc57954d3b072aebb4">Offset</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlight">          Relocs.push&#95;back(Rel);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><span class="doxyHighlight">        &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sampleprof/#a702f69807459cc25db5754a5f179d3fcaf6fbeb8fa9f451468611536b00878d41">Base</a> += (CHAR&#95;BIT &#42; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(Entry) - 1) &#42; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(Addr);</span></CodeLine>
